label.value: central B cell receptor editing

value.value: Receptor editing occurring in B cells in the bone marrow.

label.value: central T cell tolerance induction

value.value: Tolerance induction of T cells in the thymus.

label.value: tolerance induction to self antigen

value.value: Tolerance induction directed at self antigens.

label.value: B cell tolerance induction

value.value: A process involving any mechanism for tolerance induction in B cells.

label.value: B cell anergy

value.value: Any process contributing to anergy in B cells, a state of functional inactivation which is part of B cell tolerance induction.

label.value: B cell deletion

value.value: The apoptotic death of B cells which is part of B cell tolerance induction.

label.value: T cell tolerance induction

value.value: A process involving any mechanism for tolerance induction in T cells.

label.value: lymphocyte chemotaxis across high endothelial venule

value.value: The movement of a lymphocyte to cross a high endothelial venule in response to an external stimulus.

label.value: natural killer cell tolerance induction

value.value: Tolerance induction of natural killer cells.

label.value: immune system development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an organismal system whose objective is to provide calibrated responses by an organism to a potential internal or invasive threat, over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A system is a regularly interacting or interdependent group of organs or tissues that work together to carry out a given biological process.

label.value: leukocyte differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized hemopoietic precursor cell acquires the specialized features of a leukocyte. A leukocyte is an achromatic cell of the myeloid or lymphoid lineages capable of ameboid movement, found in blood or other tissue.

label.value: leukocyte migration involved in immune response

value.value: The movement of a leukocyte within or between different tissues and organs of the body as part of an immune response.

label.value: leukocyte migration involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The movement of a leukocyte within or between different tissues and organs of the body contributing to an inflammatory response.

label.value: hypersensitivity

value.value: An inflammatory response to an exogenous environmental antigen or an endogenous antigen initiated by the adaptive immune system.

label.value: acute inflammatory response to non-antigenic stimulus

value.value: An acute inflammatory response to non-antigenic stimuli such as heat or physical trauma.

label.value: acute inflammatory response

value.value: Inflammation which comprises a rapid, short-lived, relatively uniform response to acute injury or antigenic challenge and is characterized by accumulations of fluid, plasma proteins, and granulocytic leukocytes. An acute inflammatory response occurs within a matter of minutes or hours, and either resolves within a few days or becomes a chronic inflammatory response.

label.value: vasodilation involved in acute inflammatory response

value.value: An increase in the internal diameter of blood vessels, especially arterioles or capillaries, usually resulting in a decrease in blood pressure contributing to an acute inflammatory response.

label.value: regulation of vascular permeability involved in acute inflammatory response

value.value: Any process that modulates the extent to which blood vessels can be pervaded by fluid contributing to an acute inflammatory response.

label.value: regulation of plasma kallikrein-kinin cascade

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the plasma kallikrein-kinin cascade.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure involved in acute-phase response

value.value: Any process that modulates the force with which blood travels through the circulatory system that contributes to the acute phase response. The acute phase response occurs during the early phases of an infection and is marked by changes in the production of plasma proteins such as C-reactive protein.

label.value: regulation of heart contraction involved in acute-phase response

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of heart contraction that contributes to the acute phase response. The acute phase response occurs during the early phases of an infection and is marked by changes in the production of plasma proteins such as C-reactive protein.

label.value: production of molecular mediator involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The synthesis or release of any molecular mediator of the inflammatory response following an inflammatory stimulus, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: lysosomal enzyme secretion involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The regulated release of lysosomal enzymes by a cell as part of an inflammatory response.

label.value: cytokine production involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The synthesis or release of a cytokine following a inflammatory stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: respiratory burst involved in inflammatory response

value.value: A phase of elevated metabolic activity, during which oxygen consumption increases following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response; this leads to the production, by an NADH dependent system, of hydrogen peroxide (H2O2), superoxide anions and hydroxyl radicals, resulting in an increase in their intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: nitric oxide production involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The synthesis or release of nitric oxide following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: arachidonate metabolite production involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The synthesis or release of products of arachidonic acid metabolism following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in their intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: prostaglandin production involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The synthesis or release of any prostaglandin following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: leukotriene production involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The synthesis or release of any leukotriene following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: activation of plasma proteins involved in acute inflammatory response

value.value: Any process activating plasma proteins by proteolysis as part of an acute inflammatory response.

label.value: Factor XII activation

value.value: Any process that activates Factor XII (Hageman factor). Factor XII is a protein synthesized by the liver that circulates in an inactive form until it encounters collagen or basement membrane or activated platelets (as occurs at the site of endothelial injury). Factor XII then undergoes a conformational change (becoming factor XIIa), exposing an active serine center that can subsequently cleave protein substrates and activate a variety of mediator systems. Factor XII is a participant in the clotting cascade as well as the kinin cascade.

label.value: activation of blood coagulation via clotting cascade

value.value: Any process that initiates the clotting cascade of blood coagulation, a cascade of plasma enzymes that is triggered following damage to blood vessels, leading to formation of a clot.

label.value: chronic inflammatory response

value.value: Inflammation of prolonged duration (weeks or months) in which active inflammation, tissue destruction, and attempts at repair are proceeding simultaneously. Although it may follow acute inflammation, chronic inflammation frequently begins insidiously, as a low-grade, smoldering, often asymptomatic response.

label.value: chronic inflammatory response to non-antigenic stimulus

value.value: A chronic inflammatory response to a non-antigenic stimulus such as heat or physical trauma.

label.value: negative regulation of tissue kallikrein-kinin cascade

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of the tissue kallikrein-kinin cascade.

label.value: positive regulation of tissue kallikrein-kinin cascade

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of the tissue kallikrein-kinin cascade.

label.value: monocyte chemotaxis

value.value: The movement of a monocyte in response to an external stimulus.

label.value: negative regulation of plasma kallikrein-kinin cascade

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of the plasma kallikrein-kinin cascade.

label.value: positive regulation of plasma kallikrein-kinin cascade

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of the plasma kallikrein-kinin cascade.

label.value: mast cell chemotaxis

value.value: The movement of a mast cell in response to an external stimulus.

label.value: serotonin secretion by mast cell

value.value: The regulated release of serotonin by a mast cell or group of mast cells.

label.value: histamine secretion by mast cell

value.value: The regulated release of histamine by a mast cell or group of mast cells.

label.value: serotonin secretion by platelet

value.value: The regulated release of serotonin by a platelet or group of platelets.

label.value: histamine secretion by platelet

value.value: The regulated release of histamine by a platelet or group of platelets.

label.value: serotonin secretion by basophil

value.value: The regulated release of serotonin by a basophil or group of basophils.

label.value: histamine secretion by basophil

value.value: The regulated release of histamine by a basophil or group of basophils.

label.value: type I hypersensitivity mediated by mast cells

value.value: An inflammatory response driven by antigen recognition by antibodies bound to Fc receptors on mast cells, occurring within minutes after exposure of a sensitized individual to the antigen, and leading to the release of a variety of inflammatory mediators such as histamines.

label.value: type I hypersensitivity mediated by basophils

value.value: An inflammatory response driven by antigen recognition by antibodies bound to Fc receptors basophils, occurring within minutes after exposure of a sensitized individual to the antigen, and leading to the release of a variety of inflammatory mediators such as histamines.

label.value: basophil mediated immunity

value.value: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by a basophil.

label.value: basophil degranulation

value.value: The regulated exocytosis of secretory granules containing preformed mediators such as histamine, serotonin, and neutral proteases by a basophil.
